        <mxCell id="desc_text" value="5.1 Initialize Campaign - Set up fuzzing environment, configure sanitizers, allocate resources, and prepare execution parameters&#xa;&#xa;5.2 Prepare Corpus - Load seed files, generate initial test cases, and organize corpus directory structure&#xa;&#xa;5.3 Execute Fuzzer - Run LibFuzzer with configured harnesses, sanitizers, and fuzzing parameters (iterations, timeout, memory limits)&#xa;&#xa;5.4 Monitor Execution - Track fuzzing progress, resource usage, execution speed, and corpus growth in real-time&#xa;&#xa;5.5 Detect Crashes - Identify crashes, hangs, and sanitizer violations; capture crash inputs and stack traces&#xa;&#xa;5.6 Collect Coverage - Gather code coverage data, track new edges discovered, and measure fuzzing effectiveness&#xa;&#xa;5.7 Generate Campaign Report - Compile fuzzing statistics, crash summaries, coverage metrics, and execution timeline" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=10;whiteSpace=wrap;" vertex="1" parent="1">
